ide an unparalleled perspective on what it means to be Cuban.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCuban poetryvTranslations into English. 0aCuban poetryxTranslations into English. 0aCuban poetry. 7aPOETRY / Anthologies (multiple authors).2bisacsh  aanton arrufat.  abelkis cuza male.  abilingual poetry.  acarlos galindo lena.  acesar lopez.  acintio vitier.  acuban poetry.  aeliseo diego.  aengaging.  aeugenio florit.  afayad jamis.  afina garcia marruz.  agaston baquero.  aheberto padilla.  ajose alvarez baragano.  ajose kozer.  ajose lezama lima.  alorenzo garcia vega.  amiguel barnet.  anancy morejon.  anicolas guillen.  aomar perez.  apage turner.  apoetry collection.  apoetry.  araul hernandez novas.  aroberto branley.  aroberto fernandez retamar.  asamuel feijoo.  aspanish english poetry.  avirgilio pinera.1 aWeiss, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094453440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944534423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944534/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles